   <text>
      <body>
         
            
               <p>A native of <placeName>Heacham, Norfolk</placeName>, Atmore entered the itinerant
                  ministry in <date when="1781">1781</date> (see <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>,
                  10:507). He soon became one of <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s 'inner cabinet' and in <date when="1786">1786</date>
                  <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>Wesley</persName> ordained him for
                  ministry in <placeName>Scotland</placeName>. He played an active role in Methodist
                  matters after <persName>
                            <ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>'s
                  death, including a time as President of Conference. See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 36–37; <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date when="1826">1826</date>), 6:111; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 14.</p>
            
         
